## 3. Robustness Hardening Specifications (Pre-Implementation)

This section documents the planned hardening work to reduce gaps versus Kubernetes-grade robustness.
These are specifications only and are intentionally listed before implementation.

### 3.1 Gap Summary

| Area | Current behavior | Target behavior |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Reconciliation model | Runbook-triggered and mostly one-shot | Continuous reconcile loop with periodic drift checks and remediation |
| Recovery automation | Service/container restart behavior only | Policy-driven remediation graph with bounded retries and cooldowns |
| Desired vs observed state | Implicit in scripts/config | Explicit state model with conditions and transition timestamps |
| Rollouts and rollback | Manual/implicit | Stage-gated rollout flow with health gates and rollback criteria |
| Secrets lifecycle | `.env` + runtime reads | Rotation-ready, validated secret contract and audit-friendly handling |
| Workflow durability | Process-bound execution | Checkpointed pipelines that resume safely after interruption |
| Concurrency safety | Best effort | Explicit runbook locks and idempotency keys for mutating flows |
| Observability | Stage prints and command failures | Structured events + metrics per stage and policy outcome |
| Policy guardrails | Implicit conventions | Preflight schema and policy checks before startup/restore/reset |
| Failure testing | Smoke/integration focused | Fault-injection tests for drift, dependency outage, and partial failure |

### 3.2 Design Goals

1. Preserve existing runbook UX while adding stronger control-plane guarantees.
2. Keep orchestration concerns in orchestrators/managers, not toolbox functions.
3. Keep declarative config (`compose/*.yml`, `infra/permissions.yml`, `.env`) as source-of-truth artifacts.
4. Ensure every remediation and retry decision is observable and testable.

### 3.3 Proposed Architecture Additions

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  RB[runbook/* orchestrators] --> MGR[reconcile manager loop]
  MGR --> ST[state store\ndesired/observed/conditions]
  MGR --> POL[policy engine\nretry/backoff/cooldown]
  MGR --> ACT[toolbox actions\npermissions/health/post-start]
  MGR --> EVT[event + metrics sink]
  CFG[compose + infra + env] --> MGR
  ACT --> OBS[system observed state]
  OBS --> MGR
```

### 3.4 Implementation Backlog (Phased)

#### Phase 1: Control and Safety Foundations

1. Add a manager loop service that evaluates drift and reconciliation intervals.
2. Add a state document (`desired`, `observed`, `conditions`, `lastTransitionTime`) persisted per workflow.
3. Add runbook lock strategy for `start/stop/backup/restore/_reset` mutual exclusion.
4. Add idempotency tokens for mutating operations and resumable checkpoints.

#### Phase 2: Policy and Recovery

1. Add remediation policy definitions (restart/retry/escalate/fail) per stage.
2. Add bounded retries with exponential backoff and cooldown windows.
3. Add preflight validation gates for compose/permissions/env invariants.
4. Add rollback criteria for failed startup/restore stage transitions.

#### Phase 3: Observability and Verification

1. Emit structured events for each stage transition and policy decision.
2. Add per-stage counters/timers (success, failure, retries, time-to-healthy).
3. Expand tests with fault injection scenarios (docker unavailable, missing secret, drift, partial restore).
4. Add a reliability report summarizing MTTR-oriented signals per run.

### 3.5 Initial File Targeting (Planning)

| File / Area | Planned responsibility |
| --- | --- |
| `runbook/start.py`, `runbook/restore.py`, `runbook/_reset.py` | Integrate manager checkpoints and lock acquisition |
| `src/utils/permissions.py` | Manager-compatible apply interface with structured outcomes |
| `src/utils/docker/health.py` | Standardize health condition outputs for policy engine consumption |
| `src/utils/runtime.py` | Runtime paths for state/checkpoint/lock artifacts |
| `tests/test_start.py`, `tests/test_runtime_health.py`, `tests/test_restore_*` | Add hardening and fault-injection test coverage |
| `docs/project-architecture.md` | Reflect manager-loop and state-model additions after implementation |

### 3.6 Non-Goals (Current Hardening Cycle)

1. Multi-node orchestration or cluster scheduling.
2. Full Kubernetes API/CRD adoption.
3. Migration away from Compose/Ansible in this phase.

### 3.7 Exit Criteria

1. Startup and restore flows recover from transient failures with bounded retries.
2. Every mutating runbook operation is lock-protected and checkpoint-resumable.
3. A single run produces structured timeline events and reliability metrics.
4. Fault-injection tests pass for defined critical failure scenarios.
